1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:45,820
=Episode 24=

16
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:09,981
Bai Liangliang!

17
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,141
Bai Liangliang!

18
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:33,141
Bai Liangliang, get out of the car!

19
00:02:34,141 --> 00:02:35,421
I have something to say to you!

20
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:41,740
Bai Liangliang, get out of the car!

21
00:02:45,861 --> 00:02:47,301
Go out and deal with it.

22
00:03:25,141 --> 00:03:26,060
Does it hurt?

23
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:30,780
Good. It should.

24
00:03:32,101 --> 00:03:33,740
I want you to feel the pain

25
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:34,900
of being struck.

26
00:03:38,701 --> 00:03:40,301
You've never hit me before.

27
00:03:44,421 --> 00:03:46,261
I couldn't bring myself to do it.

28
00:03:48,821 --> 00:03:49,821
No matter how much

29
00:03:49,821 --> 00:03:51,660
you resented or hated me,

30
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,381
no matter what you did

31
00:03:54,381 --> 00:03:55,581
or what you said,

32
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,620
I couldn't hit you.

33
00:03:59,861 --> 00:04:02,381
But I regret it now.

34
00:04:03,701 --> 00:04:04,340
I regret

35
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:06,180
not giving you this slap sooner.

36
00:04:07,421 --> 00:04:08,821
If I had slapped

37
00:04:08,821 --> 00:04:09,821
some sense into you,

38
00:04:09,821 --> 00:04:10,780
you wouldn't have turned

39
00:04:10,780 --> 00:04:12,261
into what you are today.

40
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:13,701
Into what?

41
00:04:16,340 --> 00:04:18,061
You've turned into a monster.

42
00:04:19,621 --> 00:04:21,660
A cruel and cold-blooded monster.

43
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:22,900
Fine, I'm a monster.

44
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:25,860
And you're the one who gave birth to me.

45
00:04:28,741 --> 00:04:30,141
You brought me into this world,

46
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:32,460
only to lose me.

47
00:04:33,381 --> 00:04:34,420
Then you spent

48
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:35,701
all that effort finding me.

49
00:04:36,621 --> 00:04:38,460
You exhausted

50
00:04:39,340 --> 00:04:40,980
your entire youth.

51
00:04:42,261 --> 00:04:43,061
And for what?

52
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:47,980
To realize you brought a monster
into this world.

53
00:04:50,741 --> 00:04:51,701
You're right.

54
00:04:53,141 --> 00:04:54,621
I am a monster.

55
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,220
And this is your contribution
to this world!

56
00:05:04,181 --> 00:05:05,460
My home is just up ahead.

57
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:11,340
Everyone has another side to them.

58
00:05:12,941 --> 00:05:14,460
The Bai Liangliang you all know

59
00:05:15,821 --> 00:05:18,261
has parents who supposedly
work overseas year-round.

60
00:05:19,021 --> 00:05:20,860
She'd be a girl
from a prestigious family,

61
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,300
just like Rao Yuci.

62
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:28,060
(Salted Duck)

63
00:05:29,021 --> 00:05:30,900
But the Bai Liangliang behind this door...

64
00:05:34,860 --> 00:05:36,021
I've lived on this street

65
00:05:36,021 --> 00:05:37,100
since I was a child.

66
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,780
My mother sells salted duck.

67
00:05:42,941 --> 00:05:43,860
Because of that,

68
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:46,100
I reek of that sickening, greasy

69
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:47,220
smell of duck.

70
00:05:49,701 --> 00:05:50,540
Li Mingxuan.

71
00:05:52,621 --> 00:05:54,460
Which Bai Liangliang do you truly like?

72
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:05,780
Today,

73
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,181
I've shared my secrets and my past

74
00:06:08,181 --> 00:06:09,300
with you.

75
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:11,340
In the future,

76
00:06:11,980 --> 00:06:13,181
I expect you to work hard

77
00:06:13,181 --> 00:06:14,581
for our friendship and our business.

78
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:26,501
Do you think I should be grateful
just because you're my mother?

79
00:06:28,780 --> 00:06:30,141
Let me tell you something now.

80
00:06:31,660 --> 00:06:33,581
The person
I hate most in this world is you.

81
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:49,980
What are you crying for?

82
00:06:52,141 --> 00:06:53,061
Why are you crying?

83
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,381
I'm the one who should be crying!

84
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,821
I finally had the father I dream of.

85
00:07:07,621 --> 00:07:08,501
I finally had a chance

86
00:07:08,501 --> 00:07:10,420
to live a different life.

87
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:13,141
But what did you do?

88
00:07:13,821 --> 00:07:15,061
You took the happy life

89
00:07:15,061 --> 00:07:15,780
that was

90
00:07:15,780 --> 00:07:18,021
meant to be mine and ripped it away!

91
00:07:22,701 --> 00:07:23,501
Liangliang.

92
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:27,701
You've been deluding yourself

93
00:07:28,540 --> 00:07:30,100
that the wealthy man from back then

94
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,261
was your father.

95
00:07:32,381 --> 00:07:33,621
But he wasn't.

96
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:36,900
He wasn't your father.

97
00:07:39,021 --> 00:07:39,821
Why...

98
00:07:39,821 --> 00:07:41,540
Why won't you

99
00:07:41,540 --> 00:07:43,381
just accept reality?

100
00:07:46,621 --> 00:07:47,420
Yes.

101
00:07:49,141 --> 00:07:50,900
I've been a failure as a mother.

102
00:07:52,261 --> 00:07:53,460
In my time,

103
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:56,300
I've made far too many

104
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:57,941
wrong choices.

105
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:03,300
But I have never once regretted

106
00:08:03,300 --> 00:08:05,021
having you as my daughter.

107
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,420
And I don't believe

108
00:08:07,420 --> 00:08:09,340
I've brought you any shame.

109
00:08:12,540 --> 00:08:13,340
Liang.

110
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:18,141
Stop looking down on yourself.

111
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,780
Stop using your own pain

112
00:08:20,780 --> 00:08:21,660
as an excuse

113
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:23,701
or a reason to hurt others.

114
00:08:23,701 --> 00:08:25,021
That is no reason.

115
00:08:28,021 --> 00:08:30,061
Environment only breeds
two types of people.

116
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:32,461
Some

117
00:08:34,060 --> 00:08:35,580
are always fearing their husband,

118
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:38,700
fearing independence,

119
00:08:39,341 --> 00:08:40,900
fearing everything.

120
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:43,060
They're just like you

121
00:08:43,741 --> 00:08:45,341
hiding in the shadows of society.

122
00:08:47,021 --> 00:08:47,981
And the other type

123
00:08:49,261 --> 00:08:51,461
is dragged into endless darkness,

124
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:54,341
without ever seeing any light anywhere.

125
00:09:01,180 --> 00:09:02,420
Do you really believe

126
00:09:04,141 --> 00:09:05,700
that if you weren't my daughter,

127
00:09:07,420 --> 00:09:09,580
your life would be any different?

128
00:09:10,141 --> 00:09:10,940
Of course.

129
00:09:12,621 --> 00:09:13,461
Of course!

130
00:09:15,141 --> 00:09:17,021
I would have been just like Rao Yuci.

131
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,461
No.

132
00:09:20,381 --> 00:09:21,660
I should have been even better

133
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:23,021
than Rao Yuci.

134
00:09:23,221 --> 00:09:24,741
More kindhearted.

135
00:09:24,861 --> 00:09:26,540
I could have lived a carefree,

136
00:09:26,540 --> 00:09:27,780
vibrant life.

137
00:09:29,580 --> 00:09:30,741
The whole world

138
00:09:31,540 --> 00:09:33,021
would have been filled with kindness.

139
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:35,021
The whole world would be sunshine,

140
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:36,621
without a single trace of darkness.

141
00:09:40,341 --> 00:09:41,141
Yes.

142
00:09:42,981 --> 00:09:44,660
You should have lived a carefree,

143
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:45,900
vibrant life.

144
00:09:47,021 --> 00:09:48,981
My daughter deserves all of that.

145
00:09:50,341 --> 00:09:51,141
Liangliang.

146
00:09:52,101 --> 00:09:53,501
Whatever it is you want,

147
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:54,700
Mom will give it to you.

148
00:09:55,021 --> 00:09:56,660
Whatever it is you want to do,

149
00:09:56,660 --> 00:09:58,780
I will do my best to support you,

150
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,060
as long as you don't turn into this.

151
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:03,021
Liang, we can't...

152
00:10:03,021 --> 00:10:04,420
Are you kidding me?

153
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:12,341
For my entire life,

154
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:14,861
I've only had myself to rely on.

155
00:10:16,621 --> 00:10:17,741
Only by becoming

156
00:10:17,741 --> 00:10:19,341
the person I am now

157
00:10:20,060 --> 00:10:21,261
can I finally get

158
00:10:21,261 --> 00:10:22,780
the life I've always wanted.

159
00:10:23,940 --> 00:10:25,501
The life you want?

160
00:10:25,501 --> 00:10:28,780
Does it really have to
involve hurting others?

161
00:10:28,940 --> 00:10:30,780
No one is innocent.

162
00:10:32,221 --> 00:10:33,501
Not Rao Yuci.

163
00:10:34,341 --> 00:10:35,501
And not you.

164
00:10:38,861 --> 00:10:39,660
Bai Xia.

165
00:10:39,981 --> 00:10:42,341
I never want to see you again.

166
00:10:43,141 --> 00:10:45,540
Consider you never had a daughter.

167
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:57,461
Liangliang!

168
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:05,700
Liangliang!

169
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:33,861
Mom.

170
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:37,461
(From now on, our family)

171
00:12:40,981 --> 00:12:42,580
(will live a good life together.)

172
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:50,101
She didn't take leave,
and left no message.

173
00:13:50,660 --> 00:13:51,820
We haven't reached her today.

174
00:13:58,381 --> 00:13:59,261
She's not answering

175
00:13:59,261 --> 00:14:00,141
or replying to texts.

176
00:14:00,141 --> 00:14:01,461
No one can find her.

177
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,900
Do you have any inside info?

178
00:14:03,101 --> 00:14:04,021
Regarding what?

179
00:14:06,021 --> 00:14:06,820
Bai Qingyu.

180
00:14:09,341 --> 00:14:11,400
She was high-profile in
her support for Yang Jinwan.

181
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:14,101
But after Rao Yuci disappeared,

182
00:14:14,461 --> 00:14:16,021
the tide suddenly turned.

183
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,341
She's sided with Jiang Dongchao.

184
00:14:18,501 --> 00:14:19,300
And then,

185
00:14:21,021 --> 00:14:22,700
there's Bai Liangliang's sudden return.

186
00:14:23,461 --> 00:14:24,861
So you're saying

187
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,141
they are involved
in Rao Yuci's disappearance?

188
00:14:30,180 --> 00:14:31,940
Plus, Xian Pengyu's four percent

189
00:14:32,461 --> 00:14:33,820
seems a bit strange.

190
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:37,981
If this is all true,

191
00:14:39,021 --> 00:14:39,820
then Rao Yuci

192
00:14:40,261 --> 00:14:41,780
basically betrayed Jiang Dongchao.

193
00:14:42,341 --> 00:14:43,141
Exactly.

194
00:14:46,981 --> 00:14:49,261
So I'm wondering if...

195
00:14:50,261 --> 00:14:51,060
She's in danger.

196
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:52,981
Ms. Bai.

197
00:14:54,621 --> 00:14:57,060
Whatever it takes,
arrange a meeting with Yang Jinwan.

198
00:14:58,101 --> 00:14:59,600
Regarding the tripartite cooperation,

199
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,341
I have to convince him in person.

200
00:15:22,180 --> 00:15:23,180
Is something the matter?

201
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:25,461
Mr. Jiang.

202
00:15:25,940 --> 00:15:26,820
Rao Yuci hasn't come

203
00:15:26,820 --> 00:15:28,021
to work for a week now.

204
00:15:28,021 --> 00:15:29,461
I haven't been able to reach her,

205
00:15:29,461 --> 00:15:30,221
so...

206
00:15:32,221 --> 00:15:33,520
Rao Yuci took a leave of absence.

207
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:34,580
I approved it.

208
00:15:36,981 --> 00:15:38,741
Are you sure about that, Mr. Jiang?

209
00:15:39,981 --> 00:15:40,981
The company

210
00:15:40,981 --> 00:15:41,621
never received

211
00:15:41,621 --> 00:15:42,820
her leave application.

212
00:15:43,540 --> 00:15:44,621
As the VP,

213
00:15:44,621 --> 00:15:45,180
I thought...

214
00:15:45,180 --> 00:15:46,060
You thought what?

215
00:15:47,101 --> 00:15:47,780
Was I not

216
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:48,820
clear enough just now?

217
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,700
Rao Yuci is on leave, and I approved it.

218
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:51,981
Why are you questioning it?

219
00:15:59,261 --> 00:16:00,060
Ms. Ren.

220
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,660
You've been quite close with Yu Peidong.

221
00:16:03,461 --> 00:16:04,780
I've never interfered with that.

222
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,021
But you need to know your place

223
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:08,820
and who you work for.

224
00:16:09,861 --> 00:16:10,660
Okay?

225
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:14,540
Okay, Mr. Jiang.

226
00:16:15,540 --> 00:16:16,741
Do you need anything else?

227
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:20,021
That's all. You may leave.

228
00:16:30,101 --> 00:16:32,180
If Rao Yuci shows up at the office...

229
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:37,700
Tell me immediately.

230
00:16:40,580 --> 00:16:41,381
Yes, sir.

231
00:17:00,340 --> 00:17:04,900
(Nuannuan)

232
00:17:28,261 --> 00:17:29,060
Yuci.

233
00:17:31,501 --> 00:17:32,620
Yuci, are you home?

234
00:17:38,780 --> 00:17:39,580
Yuci.

235
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,661
If you don't want to talk,
I'll stay here with you.

236
00:17:42,661 --> 00:17:43,380
Yuci?

237
00:17:51,260 --> 00:17:52,940
(Chen Mo)

238
00:17:57,820 --> 00:18:06,740
(Chen Mo)

239
00:18:25,181 --> 00:18:26,140
I'm sorry

240
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:27,221
to ask you to meet me

241
00:18:27,421 --> 00:18:28,580
on such a short notice.

242
00:18:28,580 --> 00:18:29,800
What's going on with Rao Yuci?

243
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:30,981
Why hasn't she come to work?

244
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:33,780
She was injured.

245
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,701
She said she fell.

246
00:18:34,701 --> 00:18:35,501
Is it serious?

247
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:36,990
Is she at home or in the hospital?

248
00:18:37,261 --> 00:18:38,021
Calm down.

249
00:18:38,780 --> 00:18:40,021
Let Chen Mo finish.

250
00:18:44,620 --> 00:18:45,540
She said she fell,

251
00:18:45,540 --> 00:18:46,380
but I don't buy it.

252
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,021
I wanted to ask you two

253
00:18:48,300 --> 00:18:49,181
if she's had

254
00:18:49,181 --> 00:18:50,421
any conflicts lately?

255
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:57,701
Do you have someone in mind?

256
00:18:59,380 --> 00:19:00,261
I'm not sure.

257
00:19:01,661 --> 00:19:02,580
Lately, Yuci and I

258
00:19:02,580 --> 00:19:03,780
have been having some issues.

259
00:19:05,261 --> 00:19:06,300
She refuses to see me,

260
00:19:06,461 --> 00:19:07,780
won't tell me anything,

261
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:08,860
and I can't reach her.

262
00:19:10,380 --> 00:19:11,580
I know how she is.

263
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,661
She always wants to handle things alone.

264
00:19:15,181 --> 00:19:16,580
But it's been many days now.

265
00:19:17,701 --> 00:19:19,340
I also feel like something is wrong.

266
00:19:19,340 --> 00:19:19,701
Lately...

267
00:19:19,701 --> 00:19:20,421
Chen Mo.

268
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:22,501
We don't know

269
00:19:22,501 --> 00:19:23,701
what's going on either.

270
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:25,140
But I think,

271
00:19:25,461 --> 00:19:26,820
if Yuci doesn't want to see you,

272
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:28,021
she must have her reasons.

273
00:19:28,741 --> 00:19:30,140
Give her a little more time.

274
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:31,780
If we get any

275
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:32,661
new information,

276
00:19:32,901 --> 00:19:34,140
we'll update you immediately.

277
00:19:35,181 --> 00:19:35,701
Alright.

278
00:19:35,701 --> 00:19:36,421
Anyway,

279
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:38,501
that's how things stand.

280
00:19:38,501 --> 00:19:39,380
Sorry to bother you both.

281
00:19:39,380 --> 00:19:41,340
I've settled the bill. I have to go.

282
00:19:41,461 --> 00:19:42,261
Thanks.

283
00:19:48,140 --> 00:19:48,981
What's your problem?

284
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:50,261
Why wouldn't you let me speak?

285
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:53,941
Peidong.

286
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:56,501
I went to

287
00:19:56,501 --> 00:19:57,701
Jiang Dongchao's office today.

288
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:02,461
(He replaced his carpet.)

289
00:20:04,580 --> 00:20:05,380
(And...)

290
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:08,021
(His entire golf bag)

291
00:20:08,021 --> 00:20:08,901
(is gone.)

292
00:20:10,181 --> 00:20:11,140
(When I asked about)

293
00:20:11,140 --> 00:20:12,901
(why Rao Yuci
hasn't been coming to work,)

294
00:20:13,620 --> 00:20:14,981
(he was incredibly brusque.)

295
00:20:16,181 --> 00:20:17,461
(And he told me)

296
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:18,741
(that Rao Yuci)

297
00:20:19,140 --> 00:20:20,380
(requested leave from him.)

298
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:22,501
The carpet and gold bag...

299
00:20:32,421 --> 00:20:33,860
I'll check the surveillance footage.

300
00:20:34,060 --> 00:20:34,860
Get back here.

301
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:36,100
Get back here!

302
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:37,620
Sit down.

303
00:20:39,901 --> 00:20:40,701
Sit down.

304
00:20:45,901 --> 00:20:47,140
You're getting on my nerves.

305
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,100
If this really was

306
00:20:51,100 --> 00:20:52,300
Jiang Dongchao's doing,

307
00:20:52,860 --> 00:20:53,820
he would have made sure

308
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:54,901
everything was wiped clean.

309
00:20:54,901 --> 00:20:56,140
We won't find a shred of evidence.

310
00:20:56,140 --> 00:20:57,221
You need to calm down.

311
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,140
It's best

312
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:02,100
we don't tell Chen Mo yet.

313
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,181
I'm worried

314
00:21:03,901 --> 00:21:04,580
he'll be

315
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:05,661
reckless.

316
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,501
Just stay quiet for a bit.

317
00:21:32,421 --> 00:21:33,221
Ms. Chen.

318
00:21:43,701 --> 00:21:45,181
Why won't you answer my calls?

319
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:48,620
I was at home. It wasn't a good time.

320
00:21:51,181 --> 00:21:51,941
I almost thought

321
00:21:51,941 --> 00:21:53,300
you were avoiding me.

322
00:21:55,741 --> 00:21:56,540
Get out.

323
00:22:13,701 --> 00:22:14,501
Go over there.

324
00:22:23,820 --> 00:22:24,661
Mr. Jiang.

325
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,661
I don't believe having
Baiye Group send Bai Liangliang

326
00:22:26,661 --> 00:22:28,340
to the Bosi acquisition project

327
00:22:28,620 --> 00:22:29,580
is appropriate.

328
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:31,221
You should refuse her.

329
00:22:31,741 --> 00:22:32,701
Who'd be "appropriate"?

330
00:22:34,461 --> 00:22:35,261
You?

331
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:38,941
After Bai Liangliang left Lysen,

332
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,780
she immediately went to Bai Qingyu.

333
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:42,860
For her to return now,

334
00:22:43,340 --> 00:22:44,860
I'm afraid she has hidden motives.

335
00:22:44,941 --> 00:22:46,100
Didn't you also leave Lysen

336
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,060
only to come back later?

337
00:22:47,901 --> 00:22:49,140
Bai Liangliang facilitated

338
00:22:49,501 --> 00:22:51,340
the cooperation
between Lysen and Baiye Group.

339
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:52,661
What about you?

340
00:22:53,860 --> 00:22:56,380
Aside from making money
you shouldn't have in these projects,

341
00:22:57,060 --> 00:22:58,140
what have you actually done?

342
00:23:01,340 --> 00:23:02,501
We suspect there are issues

343
00:23:02,540 --> 00:23:04,820
with certain projects
you previously handled.

344
00:23:05,421 --> 00:23:06,100
Everyone else

345
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:07,340
in Investment Dept 2

346
00:23:07,340 --> 00:23:09,500
is cooperating
with our HR department's investigation.

347
00:23:10,580 --> 00:23:12,140
Every project we've done

348
00:23:12,181 --> 00:23:13,960
was carried out
after a contract was signed.

349
00:23:14,181 --> 00:23:15,140
If there were issues,

350
00:23:15,320 --> 00:23:16,780
it's impossible that we'd sign them.

351
00:23:16,780 --> 00:23:17,620
Impossible?

352
00:23:18,860 --> 00:23:20,941
Unless someone worked an inside job
to make money

353
00:23:21,901 --> 00:23:23,021
they shouldn't have.

354
00:23:28,501 --> 00:23:30,100
I did things I shouldn't have.

355
00:23:31,421 --> 00:23:33,060
But I've paid the price for that.

356
00:23:33,421 --> 00:23:34,780
I will never do it again.

357
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:37,421
Now that I'm back at Lysen Group,

358
00:23:38,140 --> 00:23:39,990
I am solely focused
on Lysen Group's interests

359
00:23:40,701 --> 00:23:42,300
and yours.

360
00:23:42,901 --> 00:23:43,741
Mr. Jiang.

361
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:46,981
You know how much I've done

362
00:23:47,540 --> 00:23:48,820
to redeem myself.

363
00:23:49,421 --> 00:23:51,380
And I have allowed you to stay.

364
00:23:59,860 --> 00:24:01,221
But our relationship

365
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:04,380
is different from the others, isn't it?

366
00:24:07,261 --> 00:24:08,540
I am the one person

367
00:24:09,901 --> 00:24:11,300
you can trust most.

368
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:13,380
Can you bear to let Bai Liangliang

369
00:24:13,780 --> 00:24:15,380
flaunt her power over me every day?

370
00:24:17,060 --> 00:24:17,941
Doesn't that make

371
00:24:17,941 --> 00:24:19,021
you look bad too?

372
00:24:20,421 --> 00:24:21,221
Chen Xi.

373
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:26,501
I've always known
you weren't that bright.

374
00:24:27,461 --> 00:24:28,461
But I didn't realize

375
00:24:29,701 --> 00:24:30,941
you could be this stupid.

376
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:35,501
It's a game for adults.

377
00:24:35,501 --> 00:24:36,701
You don't even know the rules.

378
00:24:37,300 --> 00:24:38,421
What makes you think

379
00:24:38,741 --> 00:24:39,421
you'd become

380
00:24:39,421 --> 00:24:40,701
the person I trust most?

381
00:24:48,661 --> 00:24:49,461
Look at me.

382
00:24:52,941 --> 00:24:53,741
Listen carefully.

383
00:24:54,661 --> 00:24:55,780
Emotionally speaking,

384
00:24:57,060 --> 00:24:57,981
I have a family.

385
00:24:58,380 --> 00:24:59,580
I have a wife and a daughter.

386
00:25:00,501 --> 00:25:02,021
They are the only ones I trust.

387
00:25:02,620 --> 00:25:03,580
Professionally,

388
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,620
Bai Liangliang has actual talent.

389
00:25:06,421 --> 00:25:08,140
If she is your leader on a project,

390
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:09,620
it means you're not as good as her.

391
00:25:10,540 --> 00:25:12,390
What does that have
to do with my reputation?

392
00:25:23,820 --> 00:25:25,501
So, in your eyes, Mr. Jiang...

393
00:25:26,620 --> 00:25:27,580
I, Chen Xi,

394
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:30,860
am worth nothing.

395
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:33,181
You should be

396
00:25:33,181 --> 00:25:34,340
well aware of your own worth.

397
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:45,580
I see.

398
00:25:46,661 --> 00:25:47,540
Mr. Jiang.

399
00:26:03,820 --> 00:26:04,620
I know

400
00:26:05,461 --> 00:26:06,901
that in your heart,

401
00:26:07,501 --> 00:26:09,021
we are no different from strangers.

402
00:26:10,540 --> 00:26:11,540
But what if

403
00:26:12,021 --> 00:26:13,981
your wife found out about us?

404
00:26:19,181 --> 00:26:20,501
I wonder what she would think?

405
00:26:23,501 --> 00:26:24,300
Wait a minute.

406
00:26:30,660 --> 00:26:34,740
(Lingling)

407
00:26:41,941 --> 00:26:43,140
Hello, Dongchao?

408
00:26:44,540 --> 00:26:45,340
Lingling.

409
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:47,540
My subordinate, Chen Xi,

410
00:26:48,181 --> 00:26:49,261
has something to tell you.

411
00:26:52,261 --> 00:26:53,060
Hello?

412
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,501
Speak up.

413
00:26:57,461 --> 00:26:58,261
It's nothing.

414
00:26:58,421 --> 00:26:59,620
She probably just forgot.

415
00:27:00,021 --> 00:27:01,461
I'm coming home early today

416
00:27:01,501 --> 00:27:02,901
to have dinner with you and Chloe.

417
00:27:03,300 --> 00:27:04,100
I see.

418
00:27:04,540 --> 00:27:05,340
Love you.

419
00:27:15,981 --> 00:27:16,981
Know your place,

420
00:27:17,741 --> 00:27:19,501
or begone from Lysen Group forever.

421
00:27:22,060 --> 00:27:23,100
The choice is yours.

422
00:27:37,661 --> 00:27:38,580
You can go now.

423
00:28:13,380 --> 00:28:14,860
(In the confrontation to come,)

424
00:28:16,221 --> 00:28:16,981
(I will be the one)

425
00:28:16,981 --> 00:28:18,620
(who redefines the rules.)

426
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,940
(Mr. Li)

427
00:28:31,461 --> 00:28:32,421
Hello, Mr. Li.

428
00:28:33,941 --> 00:28:35,021
Let's meet.

429
00:28:37,620 --> 00:28:39,021
(Jiang Dongchao hit me.)

430
00:28:40,540 --> 00:28:42,461
(But my injuries have
mostly healed now.)

431
00:28:43,901 --> 00:28:44,941
(Was it serious?)

432
00:28:45,300 --> 00:28:46,780
(Why didn't you go to the police?)

433
00:28:47,261 --> 00:28:48,340
(I didn't report it)

434
00:28:48,380 --> 00:28:49,580
(because I was worried)

435
00:28:50,261 --> 00:28:51,060
(that my loved ones)

436
00:28:51,060 --> 00:28:52,300
(would be dragged into this.)

437
00:28:53,221 --> 00:28:54,021
(So,)

438
00:28:54,380 --> 00:28:55,860
(I decided to handle this matter)

439
00:28:55,860 --> 00:28:57,421
(in my own way.)

440
00:29:18,780 --> 00:29:20,261
Mr. Li, welcome.

441
00:29:22,941 --> 00:29:24,021
Look at this.

442
00:29:24,060 --> 00:29:26,540
You've always wanted this project
to come to fruition.

443
00:29:26,701 --> 00:29:28,590
After all this time,
this is my first time here.

444
00:29:29,860 --> 00:29:30,661
Mr. Li.

445
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:32,860
I'm very grateful for your help.

446
00:29:33,820 --> 00:29:35,300
Actually, there's no need to thank me.

447
00:29:36,221 --> 00:29:37,100
Back then,

448
00:29:37,820 --> 00:29:40,580
my brothers and I also started out
with a street stall just like this.

449
00:29:41,100 --> 00:29:42,501
Then came the restaurant.

450
00:29:43,340 --> 00:29:45,021
And slowly, step by step,

451
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:46,981
it became the Lysen Group.

452
00:29:48,701 --> 00:29:50,261
Since my very first day at Lysen Group,

453
00:29:51,701 --> 00:29:53,261
I've known your story well.

454
00:30:00,060 --> 00:30:02,540
I can empathize with how you feel
when you see these people.

455
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:05,901
(Mr. Li.)

456
00:30:06,261 --> 00:30:07,060
(In fact,)

457
00:30:07,380 --> 00:30:08,981
(you've personally witnessed this era.)

458
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:12,221
(Li's Restaurant was your family's)

459
00:30:12,221 --> 00:30:13,701
(first source of wealth.)

460
00:30:14,540 --> 00:30:16,060
(After twenty years of toiling,)

461
00:30:16,221 --> 00:30:18,540
(Li's Restaurant)
(Lysen went from an industry leader)

462
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:20,181
(to gradually becoming)

463
00:30:20,181 --> 00:30:21,501
(a massive conglomerate)

464
00:30:21,860 --> 00:30:23,941
(involving shipping logistics,)

465
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:25,501
(fisheries, food processing,)

466
00:30:25,501 --> 00:30:26,860
(and mining investment.)

467
00:30:27,741 --> 00:30:29,060
(However, as the group expanded,)

468
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:30,860
(it also harbored a crisis.)

469
00:30:31,421 --> 00:30:32,421
(Li's Restaurant)
(The shrinkage of the real economy)

470
00:30:32,421 --> 00:30:33,450
(due to industrial shifts)

471
00:30:33,461 --> 00:30:35,501
(caused Lysen's growth
to hit a bottleneck.)

472
00:30:35,981 --> 00:30:36,780
(That's why,)

473
00:30:37,021 --> 00:30:38,421
(ten years ago,)

474
00:30:38,580 --> 00:30:40,820
(you initiated
the joint-stock reform for Lysen.)

475
00:30:43,780 --> 00:30:45,021
I didn't expect a youngster

476
00:30:45,021 --> 00:30:45,941
to understand

477
00:30:46,261 --> 00:30:47,380
the painstaking effort

478
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:48,741
I've put into this business.

479
00:30:49,421 --> 00:30:50,221
Sir!

480
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:51,501
Freshly cooked crawfish.

481
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:52,461
Absolutely delicious. Try some!

482
00:30:52,461 --> 00:30:53,100
Alright. Thank you.

483
00:30:53,100 --> 00:30:53,741
Sir.

484
00:30:53,741 --> 00:30:54,780
Try our malatang.

485
00:30:54,780 --> 00:30:56,060
Pure green ingredients.

486
00:30:56,060 --> 00:30:56,820
Okay.

487
00:30:56,820 --> 00:30:57,701
Thank you.

488
00:30:57,701 --> 00:30:59,100
Try a refreshing cold side dish too!

489
00:30:59,100 --> 00:31:00,421
Have some of our grilled skewers!

490
00:31:00,421 --> 00:31:01,140
Try my cold appetizers.

491
00:31:01,140 --> 00:31:02,261
Try the wontons I made.

492
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:03,340
They're really good!

493
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:04,261
So much food!

494
00:31:04,380 --> 00:31:05,140
Eat up!

495
00:31:05,140 --> 00:31:05,701
Thank you.

496
00:31:05,701 --> 00:31:06,380
Thank you so much.

497
00:31:06,380 --> 00:31:08,021
And our fruit bowl as well!

498
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:08,820
Alright, alright.

499
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:10,021
Thank you.

500
00:31:10,620 --> 00:31:12,060
Many thanks!

501
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:14,981
They're all coming here because of you.

502
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:16,461
This is all thanks to you.

503
00:31:17,221 --> 00:31:18,060
Please, have a taste.

504
00:31:18,261 --> 00:31:19,060
Okay.

505
00:31:25,860 --> 00:31:26,661
It's delicious.

506
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:29,421
I believe

507
00:31:30,501 --> 00:31:31,780
this is what Lysen Group

508
00:31:32,421 --> 00:31:33,421
should be doing.

509
00:31:34,421 --> 00:31:35,461
Our original intention

510
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:37,941
was to have a sense of responsibility

511
00:31:38,021 --> 00:31:39,380
and commitment toward this society.

512
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:41,820
Unlike Lysen Group as it is now.

513
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:45,380
The shareholders

514
00:31:46,100 --> 00:31:47,540
all believe Jiang Dongchao

515
00:31:47,540 --> 00:31:48,741
is the one making them money,

516
00:31:49,580 --> 00:31:51,340
leading Lysen Group
on an upward trajectory.

517
00:31:51,941 --> 00:31:52,981
They haven't seen

518
00:31:53,540 --> 00:31:54,741
Jiang Dongchao's ambitions.

519
00:31:55,780 --> 00:31:56,860
If this continues,

520
00:31:57,340 --> 00:31:58,580
he will lead Lysen Group into

521
00:31:58,580 --> 00:31:59,860
an extremely dangerous spot.

522
00:32:01,060 --> 00:32:03,100
Even though Jiang Dongchao
is a great storyteller,

523
00:32:03,501 --> 00:32:04,901
and Lysen Group's financial reports

524
00:32:04,901 --> 00:32:05,941
look excellent...

525
00:32:06,421 --> 00:32:07,221
However...

526
00:32:07,941 --> 00:32:09,580
The money invested in overseas projects

527
00:32:09,580 --> 00:32:10,701
has completely vanished.

528
00:32:14,181 --> 00:32:15,060
You're right.

529
00:32:15,780 --> 00:32:17,741
Jiang Dongchao is indeed
a gifted storyteller.

530
00:32:18,250 --> 00:32:19,221
(He's built the persona)

531
00:32:19,221 --> 00:32:20,820
(of a triumphant entrepreneur.)

532
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,820
(On one hand, he emphasizes)

533
00:32:26,820 --> 00:32:28,701
(his background in overseas industry,)

534
00:32:28,981 --> 00:32:30,300
We'll make Wall Street

535
00:32:30,300 --> 00:32:32,060
sit up and take notice of

536
00:32:32,060 --> 00:32:33,060
us Chinese people.

537
00:32:33,901 --> 00:32:35,300
I come from Wall Street.

538
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:36,890
Have I ever lost
in these past ten years?

539
00:32:37,620 --> 00:32:38,590
(And on the other hand,)

540
00:32:38,620 --> 00:32:40,701
(he highlights
his own sense of national sentiment.)

541
00:32:41,181 --> 00:32:43,380
Should our vibrant national enterprise

542
00:32:43,380 --> 00:32:44,941
lose its fighting spirit like this?

543
00:32:45,580 --> 00:32:46,461
Everything we do

544
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:48,421
is a commitment to our hometown

545
00:32:48,661 --> 00:32:49,860
and to every single investor

546
00:32:49,860 --> 00:32:50,701
in our company.

547
00:32:51,181 --> 00:32:54,300
Lysen Group will always stand
with justice,

548
00:32:54,701 --> 00:32:55,860
protecting every cent

549
00:32:55,860 --> 00:32:57,380
of our investors' hard-earned money.

550
00:32:57,741 --> 00:32:58,981
(On the surface, he appears)

551
00:32:59,421 --> 00:33:00,501
(to be a perfectly composed)

552
00:33:00,941 --> 00:33:01,981
(and masterful strategist.)

553
00:33:03,060 --> 00:33:04,181
(But based on my analysis,)

554
00:33:04,741 --> 00:33:06,501
(behind his painstaking facade)

555
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:09,501
(is a gray area we can uncover.)

556
00:33:13,021 --> 00:33:13,820
I know

557
00:33:14,620 --> 00:33:15,820
you also suspect Jiang Dongchao

558
00:33:15,820 --> 00:33:16,701
has been exploiting

559
00:33:16,701 --> 00:33:17,741
Lysen Group's projects

560
00:33:17,741 --> 00:33:18,860
to line his own pockets.

561
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:20,380
Am I right?

562
00:33:23,060 --> 00:33:24,661
I certainly didn't misjudge you.

563
00:33:25,340 --> 00:33:26,901
I hope you can help me find

564
00:33:27,461 --> 00:33:29,300
the loopholes
in Jiang Dongchao's finances.

565
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:32,540
That's why I need
to return to Lysen Group

566
00:33:33,100 --> 00:33:34,140
to investigate

567
00:33:34,941 --> 00:33:36,780
his overseas investment projects.

568
00:33:37,701 --> 00:33:38,380
Right now,

569
00:33:38,380 --> 00:33:39,060
he's desperate to

570
00:33:39,060 --> 00:33:40,620
push through the tripartite cooperation

571
00:33:41,100 --> 00:33:42,620
for personal gain.

572
00:33:44,140 --> 00:33:46,021
If he slips up this time,

573
00:33:48,021 --> 00:33:48,820
it might be

574
00:33:49,421 --> 00:33:50,780
our best opportunity.

575
00:33:55,580 --> 00:33:59,380
=Episode 24=
(If the Questions Had Stopped Then)

576
00:33:59,901 --> 00:34:02,341
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

577
00:34:02,341 --> 00:34:08,541
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

578
00:34:09,301 --> 00:34:12,501
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

579
00:34:12,501 --> 00:34:17,021
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

580
00:34:17,021 --> 00:34:24,541
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

581
00:34:24,541 --> 00:34:28,461
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

582
00:34:28,461 --> 00:34:32,501
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

583
00:34:32,501 --> 00:34:36,021
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

584
00:34:36,021 --> 00:34:39,981
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

585
00:34:39,981 --> 00:34:44,141
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

586
00:34:44,141 --> 00:34:48,341
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

587
00:34:48,341 --> 00:34:52,141
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

588
00:34:52,141 --> 00:34:56,221
♪Keep walking through the light♪

589
00:34:56,221 --> 00:35:00,421
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

590
00:35:00,421 --> 00:35:06,741
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

591
00:35:23,861 --> 00:35:30,501
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

592
00:35:30,501 --> 00:35:34,341
♪An apology that came too late♪

593
00:35:34,341 --> 00:35:38,981
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

594
00:35:39,061 --> 00:35:46,461
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

595
00:35:46,461 --> 00:35:50,541
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

596
00:35:50,541 --> 00:35:54,621
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

597
00:35:54,621 --> 00:35:58,621
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

598
00:35:58,621 --> 00:36:02,381
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

599
00:36:02,381 --> 00:36:06,581
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

600
00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:10,741
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

601
00:36:10,741 --> 00:36:14,461
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

602
00:36:14,461 --> 00:36:18,501
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

603
00:36:18,501 --> 00:36:22,541
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

604
00:36:22,541 --> 00:36:28,741
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
